    <div class="body">
      <section class="sec" id="reserves">
        <h2>The Reserves: Why Venezuela Matters</h2>
        <p>Venezuela holds approximately <strong>304 billion barrels</strong> of proven oil reserves — more than Saudi Arabia, Canada, or Iran. The vast majority sits in the <strong>Orinoco Oil Belt (Faja Petrolífera del Orinoco)</strong>, a 55,000 km² formation in eastern Venezuela containing an estimated <strong>1.36 trillion barrels</strong> of original oil in place.</p>
        <p>Yet production has collapsed from a peak of 3.4 million bpd (1998) to roughly 800,000 bpd by late 2025. The gap between reserves and production represents one of the most compelling — and riskiest — investment propositions in global energy.</p>
        <p>As of April 2026, production has recovered to ~1.1M bpd, with exports reaching 1.23M bpd — a seven-year high — driven by sanctions relief and renewed foreign operator activity.</p>
        <p class="source-citation">Sources: <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/venezuela-crude-oil-production-investment.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CNBC (Jan 2026)</a> · <a href="https://energy-analytics-institute.org/2026/01/13/eai-analysis-venezuelas-55000-km2-orinoco-belt-of-faja/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Energy Analytics Institute</a> · <a href="https://www.oilandgasadvancement.com/news/venezuela-oil-exports-surge-to-seven-year-high-in-april-2026/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Oil & Gas Advancement (Apr 2026)</a></p>
      </section>

      <section class="sec" id="operators">
        <h2>Current Operators & Joint Ventures</h2>

        <div class="company-card">
          <h3>Chevron Corporation (CVX)</h3>
          <div class="cc-meta">United States · NYSE: CVX</div>
          <div class="cc-stats">
            <span><strong>Production:</strong> ~260,000 bpd</span>
            <span><strong>Share of Venezuela total:</strong> ~25%</span>
          </div>
          <p>Operates four joint ventures with PDVSA. In April 2026, executed a strategic asset swap gaining increased working interests in Petroindependencia (49%) and development rights to Ayacucho 8 in the Orinoco Belt via Petropiar (30%). Targets ~390,000 bpd within two years — a ~50% increase.</p>
          <p class="source-citation">Source: <a href="https://www.chevron.com/newsroom/2026/q2/chevron-consolidates-venezuela-heavy-oil-position-in-asset-swap" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chevron Newsroom (Apr 2026)</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="company-card">
          <h3>Repsol S.A.</h3>
          <div class="cc-meta">Spain · BME: REP</div>
          <div class="cc-stats">
            <span><strong>Production:</strong> ~45,000 bpd</span>
            <span><strong>Target:</strong> +50% within 12 months</span>
          </div>
          <p>Signed agreement in April 2026 to regain operational control of Petroquiriquire (60% PDVSA / 40% Repsol). Plans to triple production over three years. Also partners with ENI on the Cardón IV offshore gas project.</p>
          <p class="source-citation">Source: <a href="https://www.repsol.com/en/press-room/press-releases/2026/repsol-agrees-conditions-increase-oil-production-venezuela/index.cshtml" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Repsol Press Release (Apr 2026)</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="company-card">
          <h3>Eni S.p.A.</h3>
          <div class="cc-meta">Italy · BIT: ENI</div>
          <div class="cc-stats">
            <span><strong>Production:</strong> ~64,000 boepd (2025)</span>
            <span><strong>Key asset:</strong> Junín 5 (35B barrels certified)</span>
          </div>
          <p>Signed agreement in April 2026 to relaunch Junín 5 (heavy crude, Orinoco Belt) and Petrosucre projects. Also holds 50% of the Cardón IV offshore gas project with Repsol.</p>
          <p class="source-citation">Source: <a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/energy/articles/eni-signs-agreement-relaunch-heavy-195728000.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Yahoo Finance / ENI (Apr 2026)</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="company-card">
